        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tui): include pairing approval command in recovery hint (Fixes #67618)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #67618.\n\nWhen the TUI disconnects with a pairing-required error, it currently tells the user to run `openclaw devices list` and then \"approve your request ID\" without ever naming the actual approval command.\n\nThis keeps the scope narrow:\n- update the pairing recovery hint to include `openclaw devices approve <requestId>`\n- keep the status line and pairing-detection behavior unchanged\n- add a focused regression assertion on the help text\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```bash\nnode_modules/.bin/vitest run src/tui/tui.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed:\n- pairing-required TUI disconnect guidance should tell the operator the exact approval command to run after `openclaw devices list`\n\nEnvironment tested:\n- local source checkout on this branch\n\nEvidence after the fix:\n- `resolveGatewayDisconnectState()` now returns:\n  - `Pairing required. Run \\`openclaw devices list\\`, then \\`openclaw devices approve <requestId>\\`, then reconnect.`\n- `src/tui/tui.test.ts` now asserts the hint includes `openclaw devices approve <requestId>`\n\nObserved result:\n- the recovery text now names the exact CLI step instead of making the operator infer it from the pending request list\n\nWhat was not tested:\n- a live TUI pairing flow against a running gateway\n\nProof limitations:\n- the focused Vitest invocation currently fails in this checkout before tests run because of a pre-existing `getOAuthProviders is not a function` startup error outside this TUI change\n\n## Risk\n\nLow. This is a copy-only TUI hint change with a matching unit-test assertion. No pairing protocol, gateway behavior, or CLI flow changed.",
